other_tests.procedure_name: Endoscopic Ultrasound Guided Fine Needle Aspiration (EUS-guided FNA)
other_tests.findings: Cytopathological features consistent with a tumor of neuroendocrine cell origin, positive immunohistochemical staining for chromogranin A and synaptophysin.
Planned Whipple procedure was not feasible; debulking of tumor was performed with involved margins.
No LOH or copy number changes, no other deleterious genetic alterations identified.
Did not reveal any missed genetic alterations, aberrant splicing variants, gene fusions, or gene expression alterations.
Well-differentiated, WHO grade 1 NET with Ki-67 index of 12%.
Abnormal, uniformly strong cytoplasmic staining of tumor cells with virtually absent nuclear staining.
